        </div>
        <p>The core contribution is not a standalone feature set, but an integrated control plane: Iron Line L0-L7 for deterministic stage ownership, DAC tracks and stripes for structural observability, and a steno transport layer (`strip`, `pajamas`, `noBLINK`) that preserves timing-critical metadata while keeping developer ergonomics intact. On top of this foundation, the quantum gutter and 11-symbol prefix coordinates provide line-level semantic traceability, while the new `.qbit` codec contributes robustness as a fault-tolerant interchange layer with round-trip-safe encoding, formatter-aware strip/reinject handling, and reproducible decode paths for long-horizon archives and multi-client sync. The ugrad build path operationalizes these abstractions into a measurable pipeline from overclocked local base code to QPU-ready artifacts through preflight checks, backend-constrained dispatch, result validation, and memory reinjection. A second innovation axis is the Contrails keyboard advancement, which turns symbolic concept lanes into an accessible human input protocol for faster intent capture, lower operator cognitive load, and cleaner alignment between keystroke semantics, prefix coordinates, and downstream quantum/runtime transformations. In grant terms, the novelty is the closed-loop linkage of symbolic reasoning, retrieval-memory continuity, resilient codec transport, and production deployment in one reproducible surface, with clear translational value for research velocity, verification rigor, and cross-platform reliability across ugrad.ai and qbitos.ai.</p>
        <div class="eq">
          <span class="sym">|ψ<sub>out</sub>⟩ = Μ(∏<sub>i</sub> μ<sub>i</sub>) |0⟩<sup>⊗n</sup>, &nbsp; μ<sub>i</sub> ≡ U(P<sub>i</sub>, d<sub>i</sub>, c<sub>i</sub>, s<sub>i</sub>)</span>
          <span class="plain">|psi_out&gt; = M(prod_i mu_i)|0&gt;^otimes n, mu_i = U(P_i,d_i,c_i,s_i)</span>
          <div class="eq-insight">
            <h2>Canonical Macro/Micro State Equation</h2>
            <div class="eq-insight-grid">
              <img class="eq-mini-img" src="assets/machine-learning-paper-01-744f0646-d20c-4df4-9201-a24a76cdc837.png" alt="Canonical macro micro state circuit chart">
              <p><strong>Question:</strong> Do local μ operations combine into a stable global Μ state?<br><strong>Metric definition:</strong> coherence=.87, operator stability=.82, aggregate output confidence=.89 (0–1 scale).<br><strong>Decision gate:</strong> if coherence &lt; .80, hold dispatch and rerun operator weighting before cycle advance.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <section class="exec eq-walk" aria-label="Operational walkthrough for canonical macro micro state equation">
          <p class="kicker">Operational Walkthrough: Canonical Macro/Micro State Equation</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Macro state (Μ):</strong> orchestrates global routing, memory continuity, and policy gates across Iron Line layers.</li>
            <li><strong>Micro operators (μ<sub>i</sub>):</strong> per-line transforms carry prefix, depth, context, and semantic signal into execution.</li>
            <li><strong>Runtime mapping:</strong> `U(P<sub>i</sub>, d<sub>i</sub>, c<sub>i</sub>, s<sub>i</sub>)` maps directly to DAC + Prefixes + Quantum Gutter fields.</li>
            <li><strong>Product effect:</strong> one equation tracks authoring intent through `.qbit` transport into reproducible runtime behavior.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <h3>1. Core Model (Μμ)</h3>
        <p>Uppercase Mu (Μ) represents macro manifold behavior: global orchestration, routing, memory continuity, and multimodal scoring. Lowercase mu (μ) represents local operators: per-line transforms, confidence reroutes, transport decisions, and cue alignment. This split makes system-level reasoning and implementation-level behavior simultaneously auditable.</p>
        <div class="eq">
          <span class="sym">System = Μ(Σ<sub>i</sub> μ<sub>i</sub>(line<sub>i</sub>, event<sub>i</sub>))</span>
          <span class="plain">System = M(sum_i mu_i(line_i,event_i))</span>
          <div class="eq-insight">
            <h2>System Aggregation (Μ over Σμ)</h2>
            <div class="eq-insight-grid">
              <canvas class="eq-mini-canvas" width="420" height="216" data-mini-plot="cube-points-static" data-mini-y-min="0.00" data-mini-y-max="1.00" data-mini-x-min="0.00" data-mini-x-max="1.00" data-fallback-src="assets/opt-paper-02-e7e7afd8-a733-4149-94c0-d339076611de.png" aria-label="System aggregation static cube chart with axes"></canvas>
              <p><strong>Question:</strong> Is system aggregation fast and correct under load?<br><strong>Metric definition:</strong> event-fusion latency=34ms, stage assignment accuracy=97.2%.<br><strong>Decision gate:</strong> if latency &gt; 50ms or accuracy &lt; 95%, fallback to conservative routing profile.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <section class="exec eq-walk" aria-label="Operational walkthrough for system aggregation equation">
          <p class="kicker">Operational Walkthrough: System Aggregation (Μ over Σμ)</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Aggregation rule:</strong> each line/event micro-operation contributes to a single auditable macro system state.</li>
            <li><strong>Field stitching:</strong> line index + event payload + DAC track context fold into shared run identity and trace.</li>
            <li><strong>Control use:</strong> drives stage ownership, dispatch order, and memory update priority under load.</li>
            <li><strong>Product effect:</strong> keeps terminal-core behavior interpretable when parallel actions increase project stress.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <h3 id="equations">2. Derived Equation Stack - Canonical Set</h3>
        <div class="eq">
          <span class="sym sym-spot">|ψ<sub>out</sub>⟩ = (E ∘ R ∘ D ∘ T)(|ψ<sub>in</sub>⟩)</span>
          <span class="plain">|psi_out&gt; = (E o R o D o T)(|psi_in&gt;), T=detect, D=decode, R=render, E=enhance</span>
          <div class="eq-insight">
            <h2>Pipeline State Evolution</h2>
            <div class="eq-insight-grid">
              <img class="eq-mini-img" src="assets/machine-learning-paper-03-c4229434-05de-4444-90f6-b4a40e00b025.png" alt="Pipeline state evolution chart">
              <p><strong>Question:</strong> Where does cycle time concentrate in T→D→R→E?<br><strong>Metric definition:</strong> T=42ms, D=31ms, R=18ms, E=24ms (total 115ms).<br><strong>Decision gate:</strong> if total &gt; 140ms, optimize top-two contributors first (currently T and D).</p>
            </div>
