        <section class="exec" aria-label="Release governance coverage">
          <p class="kicker">Coverage: Config + Plugin + Rules + Artifacts + Codec</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Config:</strong> publish versioned runtime/build config with reproducible defaults (`pyproject.toml`, lockfiles, model/provider matrix).</li>
            <li><strong>Plugin + MCP:</strong> release plugin manifest, tool schema inventory, and capability guardrails with compatibility notes.</li>
            <li><strong>Rulesets:</strong> include machine-readable policy/rules docs for safety, formatting scope, and deployment constraints.</li>
            <li><strong>Artifacts:</strong> ship signed release artifacts with checksums, changelog, and DOI snapshot mapping.</li>
            <li><strong>Codec specifics:</strong> document `.qbit` encode/decode mode, strip/reinject behavior, round-trip tests, and schema versioning.</li>
